sec.p:
There are four main categories of surrogate:


off-budget expenditures, as when certain income sources and accumulated balances are not shown in budget documents (Kraan, 2004);

tax expenditures in the form of reduced tax liability if the taxpayer behaves in a prescribed way (OECD, 2010); for example, subsidies to owner-occupied housing through the tax system rather than by means of explicit subsidies;

coerced private expenditures, as illustrated by compulsory third-party liability insurance for car drivers; and

future commitments constructed in ways that are not currently recorded as public expenditure, such as obtaining new hospitals, roads and schools through PPPs.
